parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion or rusting of the subframe can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel feels loose or unstable
the vehicle makes unusual noises
the engine cradle is rusted
the subframe is corroded
the vehicle is unable to pass inspection
the wheel alignment is off
the vehicle is difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the airbag deploys without cause
the airbag does not deploy in the event of a crash
the passenger side airbag resistance is high
and the airbag warning light stays on intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a problem with the airbag system, which can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
